Python day6 notes 
-----------------------
Strings : Data types used to represent of textual data 
  They are sequence of characters and are enclosed in either 
       1)single quotes (' ')
       2)double quotes (" ")
       3)triple quotes (''' ''' or """ """)

String indexing : Strings are ordered sequences, and you can access individual character by using 
                  indexing. where the first character has index of 0
  it starts for 0 in forword indexing means starts from left to right and 
  it starts for -1 in Negative indexing means starts from right to left.

String Slicing : Division of String into several parts 

     Syntex for String Slicing is 
            string _Variable[start:stop:step] 

               Eg : 1) print(s[1])        6) print(s[2:])
                    2) print(s[-1])       7) print(s[:-1])
                    3) print(s[1:3])      8) print(s[::2])
                    4) print(s[1:-1])     9) print(s[1::2])
                    5) print(s[:3])      10) print(s[::-1])
                               s = hello world 
                                   012345678910
                      1) e               6) llo world
                      2) d               7) hello worl
                      3) el              8) hlowrd
                      4) ello worl       9) el ol
                      5) hel            10) dlrow olleh


String Concatenation : you can concatenate strigd using + operator 

String length : you can find the lenght of string using len() function 

